description: From Latin ēveniō (“happen, fall out, come out”), from ē (“out of, from”) (short form of ex) + veniō (“come”).

verbs.description: evene (third-person singular simple present evenes, present participle evening, simple past and past participle evened)

entries.meaning: (obsolete) To occur; to happen; to come to pass.
examples: What would evene, if an eagle that is carried by the course of the wind, should let a stone fall from its talons.
